\mt1 1 Timothy
\is1 Introduction
\ip Si Timutiyu, sabeka Kristuwanen there from Asya. Hudiyu the iney rin Grigu mule the amey rin. Tenged su nakita of Paul true/correct the faith of Timutiyu, inggimu rin sikandin duma rin and bate-bate din of pegwali and of pegpangguhud of Meupiya Panugtulen (Me Himu 16:1-3). Ne the Ipisu iya the sabeka lungsud miggendiyaan dan. Ne there ihaat of Paul si Timutiyu eyew iyan eg-uyan of believers. Te bayew e naluhey si Timutiyu there to Ipisu, migsulatan e sikandin of Paul. Me three pulu (30) buwa the idad of Timutiyu of seeye timpu.
\ip Due three tuyu of this letter of Paul ki Timutiyu:
\ip 1.) The first tuyu of Paul, migpaney-paney sikandin concerning the not true/correct teaching there to group of believers. This teaching, nenekegsewug e of me suman-suman of Jews and of non-Jews. Su sumale kandan bad the this se world mig-ugpaan ta. Ne and kun de egkaluwas the person ke due katuenan din and not egpangeen of duma klasi of egkeenen and not also eg-asawa. Migpanulu si Paul not true/correct sika.
\ip 2.) Migpanulu again the this letter concerning the carrying of group of believers and of pegsimba. Insulat here the correct egbatasanen of sabeka teacher of believers, of talagbulig of believers and of duma believers widows and me uripen.
\ip 3.) Te ending, advised din si Timutiyu ke egmenuwen egkeyimu good suluhuanen of Hisu Kristu, and concerning the katungdanan din there to Christians.
